CIBC is a leading North American financial institution with 10 million personal banking, business, public sector and institutional clients. CIBC offers a full range of advice, solutions and services in the United States, across Canada and around the world. In the U.S., CIBC Bank USA provides commercial banking, private and personal banking and small business banking solutions and CIBC Private Wealth Management offers investment management, wealth strategies and legacy planning. CIBC works to help you make your ambitions a reality with a team that is committed to being always professional, genuinely caring and collaborates to find simple solutions as we build our relationship-focused bank for the modern world. Every year, CIBC is recognized for its business success, community commitment and employee initiatives. We are proud of this success and are committed to creating an inclusive workplace and an environment where all of our team members can excel. 
 
Responsibilities:
 
Head of Risk Modeling Data is Accountable For Supporting The Chief Risk Analytics and Infrastructure Officer In The Following Oversight Activities 
Buildout the risk data team to support future ready Risk Analytics Organization using internal / external data, cloud and social era tools and techniques for data analytics, mining and visualization. 
Build out the data foundation for risk future model building capability (E.G. Credit, Operational, Enterprise, LOB) 
Work together with US Data Management Office for Risk Data Management determination and design 
Direct Ownership interactions for development and ongoing support for US Risk Data Mart(s) within US Region Data Management Office (DMO) 
Business Sponsor of risk related data programs and projects within the US Region 
Provide thought leadership and input to the US data strategy for Machine Learning (ML) and Artificial Intelligence (AI) tools and use of scanned free text fields for combining unstructured data with structured 
Prioritize for the US Data Management Office the build out of Model ready data and analytical processes for faster model development, validation and ongoing monitoring.
 KEY ACCOUNTABILITIES 
Buildout, innovate and expand risk data ownership and capabilities 
Responsible person for setting risk data agenda in Risk Analytics 
Provide risk data / analytics results directly to business users, allowing them to identify trends and insights; also freeing data specialists from mundane queries and reporting 
Participate and collaborate in the creation of a culture that promotes data-driven decisions backed by investigation and collaboration around risk data 
Ensure meeting all the Regulatory / Compliance / Accounting requirements with respect to the risk data capabilities 
Maintain awareness of upcoming or proposed industry regulatory actions and supervisory Scan the horizon for emerging analytical skills, techniques, technologies and, where appropriate, tools / data build to ensure their timely introduction for competitive advantage. 
Recruit, train / mentor and develop a high-performance risk modeling data team 
Coordinate with the US Data Management Office and Global (Parent) CIBC teams to adopt and implement the Data Governance policy and standards.
 Locate the new and/or best sources for risk data to drive more effective and efficient analytics 
COMPLIANCE REQUIREMENTS/RESPONSIBILITIES 
As an employee of CIBC, the incumbent must comply with all applicable CIBC and Line of Business policies, standards, guidelines and controls. 
AUTHORITIES/DECISION RIGHTS 
This job has the authority to recommend changes to business processes in order to enhance oversight, operational efficiency and effectiveness. 
 
